text.section:
Except as provided in subsections (c) and (d) of this section, a person who is called on for assistance in an emergency is not subject to any civil liability or penalty as a result of assistance or advice rendered in:
Mitigating the effects of an actual or threatened discharge of a hazardous substance or material;
Preventing a discharge of a hazardous substance or material;
Cleaning up a discharge of a hazardous substance or material; or
Attempting any of the acts in this subsection.
